from pytube import YouTube

# Adding dates to youtube data based on video upload date
dates = []
views = []
likes = []
titles = []
commentCounts = []
for i in range(79):
    link = "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=" + str(test['VideoID'][i])
    youtubeObject = YouTube(link)
    date = youtubeObject.publish_date
    title = youtubeObject.title
    view = youtubeObject.initial_data['contents']['twoColumnWatchNextResults']\
['results']['results']['contents'][0]['videoPrimaryInfoRenderer']['viewCount']['videoViewCountRenderer']['viewCount']['simpleText']
    like = youtubeObject.initial_data['contents']['twoColumnWatchNextResults']\
['results']['results']['contents'][0]['videoPrimaryInfoRenderer']['videoActions']['menuRenderer']['topLevelButtons'][0]\
['segmentedLikeDislikeButtonViewModel']['likeButtonViewModel']['likeButtonViewModel']['toggleButtonViewModel']['toggleButtonViewModel']\
['defaultButtonViewModel']['buttonViewModel']['title']
    commentCount = youtubeObject.initial_data['contents']['twoColumnWatchNextResults']\
['results']['results']['contents'][-2]['itemSectionRenderer']['contents'][0]['commentsEntryPointHeaderRenderer']['commentCount']\
['simpleText']
    dates.append(date)
    titles.append(title)
    views.append(view)
    likes.append(like)
    commentCounts.append(commentCount)

import nltk
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer

nltk.download('stopwords')
nltk.download('vader_lexicon')
nltk.download('wordnet')

stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
sid = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

preprocessed_comments = []

for comment in youtube['Comment']:
    # Remove URLs, mentions, and hashtags
    text = ' '.join(word for word in comment.split())
    # Remove punctuation and convert to lowercase
    text = ''.join(char for char in text if char.isalnum() or char.isspace())
    text = text.lower()
    # Tokenize text and remove stop words
    words = nltk.word_tokenize(text)
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatize words
    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    # Calculate sentiment score
    sentiment_score = sid.polarity_scores(text)['compound']
    # Add preprocessed tweet to list
    preprocessed_comments.append({'text': text, 'words': words, 'sentiment': sentiment_score})

# preprocessed_comments

from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

# Vectorize preprocessed tweets
vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()
vectorized_comments = vectorizer.fit_transform(comment['text'] for comment in preprocessed_comments)

# Cluster tweets using K-means
num_clusters = 8
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=num_clusters)
kmeans.fit(vectorized_comments)
print(kmeans.inertia_)

# Assign cluster labels to preprocessed tweets
for i, tweet in enumerate(preprocessed_comments):
    tweet['cluster'] = kmeans.labels_[i]

# Print sentiment and topic analysis
for cluster in range(num_clusters):
    cluster_tweets = [tweet for tweet in preprocessed_comments if tweet['cluster'] == cluster]
    num_tweets = len(cluster_tweets)
    avg_sentiment = sum(tweet['sentiment'] for tweet in cluster_tweets) / num_tweets
    print(f'Cluster {cluster}: {num_tweets} tweets, average sentiment = {avg_sentiment:.2f}')

stop_words = set(stopwords.words("english"))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()

def preprocess_text(text):
  words = word_tokenize(text.lower())
  words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words if word.isalnum() and word not in stop_words]
  return " ".join(words)

cleaned_comments2 = [preprocess_text(comment) for comment in youtube['Comment']]

# Build and train the sentiment analysis model
model_sentiment = Sequential()
model_sentiment.add(Embedding(len(word_index) + 1, 100, input_length=data_padded.shape[1]))
model_sentiment.add(LSTM(100))
model_sentiment.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
model_sentiment.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
model_sentiment.summary()

history = model_sentiment.fit(X_train, np.zeros(len(X_train)), epochs=5, batch_size=256, validation_data=(X_test, np.zeros(len(X_test))))
